  "time_ut": 1661074412,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0dd1 \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A person who kidnapped the owner of the travel company and robbed money was caught",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Borella police say that a group of three including two brothers who kidnapped the owner and assistant accountant of a travel company near the Bandaragama Bolgoda Bridge and robbed them of several hundred thousand rupees, posing as police officers, were arrested in Borella Vanathamulla area.",
        "According to the police, the suspects took away the credit cards of the two and robbed them of nearly 8 lakh rupees and a silver necklace.",
        "It has been revealed in the initial investigations conducted by the police that the owner of the travel agency and the assistant accountant, who was abducted on the 17th of last year, was brought near the Bolgoda bridge in Bandaragama, saying that he needed a luxury car to provide transportation facilities from Katunayake airport to a doctor coming to Sri Lanka from abroad.",
        "The police say that the three robbers who had come in a Thiroda car crossed the road to the car and pretended to be from the police and put them both in the back seat of the car and took them to a house in Vanathamulla on the pretext of taking them to the Bandaragama police.",
        "The police said that after threatening the two of them, they took the credit cards in their wallets and took two hundred thousand rupees first, then the assistant accountant took the remaining amount to Borella and took four hundred fifty eight thousand eight thousand three hundred rupees from a private bank.",
        "A police officer said that after complaining to Chief Inspector AJMR Samarasinghe, Station Commander of Borella Police regarding the robbery, the Station Commander, who acted immediately, went to a house in Borella Vanathamulla on the direction of the complainants and managed to arrest one of the suspects there.",
        "Police say that the arrested suspect was also wearing the silver necklace that had been stolen that day"
      ],
